Lanare first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lanare had a population of 540. The population density was {{convert|267.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lanare was 90 (16.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 26 (4.8%) [[African Americans|African American]], 7 (1.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 4 (0.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 312 (57.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 100 (18.5%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 496 persons (91.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lanare CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0640116 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 142 households, out of which 63 (44.4%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 73 (51.4%) were married-couple households, 11 (7.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 22 (15.5%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 36 (25.4%) had a male householder with no partner present. 23 households (16.2%) were one person, and 8 (5.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.8.<ref name=DP1/> There were 110 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (77.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lanare CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0640116 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 156 people (28.9%) under the age of 18, 57 people (10.6%) aged 18 to 24, 129 people (23.9%) aged 25 to 44, 132 people (24.4%) aged 45 to 64, and 66 people (12.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 33.7{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 108.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 149 housing units at an average density of {{convert|73.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 142 (95.3%) were occupied. Of these, 72 (50.7%) were owner-occupied, and 70 (49.3%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0640116|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715030529/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0640116|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Lanare CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Lanare had a population of 589. The population density was {{convert|291.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lanare was 181 (30.7%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 57 (9.7%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 5 (0.8%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2 (0.3%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 300 (50.9%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 44 (7.5%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 519 persons (88.1%).

The Census reported that 589 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 140 households, out of which 89 (63.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 83 (59.3%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 28 (20.0%) had a female householder with no husband present, 15 (10.7%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 14 (10.0%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 11 households (7.9%) were made up of individuals, and 5 (3.6%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 4.21.  There were 126 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (90.0% of all households); the average family size was 4.32.

The age distribution was 199 people (33.8%) under the age of 18, 62 people (10.5%) aged 18 to 24, 164 people (27.8%) aged 25 to 44, 115 people (19.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 49 people (8.3%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 28.5 years. For every 100 females, there were 95.0 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 107.4 males.

There were 147 housing units at an average density of {{convert|72.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 140 were occupied, of which 87 (62.1%) were owner-occupied, and 53 (37.9%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 1.8%.  374 people (63.5% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 215 people (36.5%) lived in rental housing units.

